==English==

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|la}} {{term|acanthus|lang=la}}, from {{etyl|grc}} {{term|ἄκανθος|tr=akanthos|sc=polytonic|lang=grc}}, from {{term|ἀκή|tr=akē||thorn|sc=polytonic|lang=grc}} + {{term|ἄνθος|tr=anthos||flower|sc=polytonic|lang=grc}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/ə.ˈkæn.θəs/}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun|pl=acanthuses|pl2=acanthi}}

# {{context|botany}} A member of the genus ''[[Acanthus]]'' of [[herbaceous]] [[prickly]] plants with toothed leaves, (family Acanthaceae, order Scrophulariales) found in the south of Europe, Asia Minor, and India.
# {{context|architecture}} An ornament resembling the [[foliage]] or leaves of ''[[Acanthus spinosus]]'', and used in the [[capital]]s of the [[Corinthian]] and [[composite]] orders.

